configset GLOBAL default_lists_format = [value]
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
GLOBAL means you are setting site parameters, not just one list
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =

(extracted on 7 Mar 1999 from configshow-comments, default value is below)

# default_lists_format /tiny,compact,short,long,enhanced/
# (short)              [enum] <lists>
# This defines the default output format for the lists command.
# compact shows one list per line with short descriptions.
# long shows long descriptions
# enhanced shows long descriptions and extra information (whether or not
#   the user is subscribed to the list, etc.)
configset GLOBAL default_lists_format = enhanced

